snippet.textDisplay: Hey Corridor😁 I’m a really big fan of your channel and I’ve really learn a lot. I know you do VFX artist react and I have an interesting potential entry that no one seems to be talking about. I don’t know if you’ve seen the movie Togo on Disney Plus, but In the movie when the background is out of focus there appears to be some sort of strange paper like texture to it. I’m pretty sure that it only shows up when something is out of focus and no where else. The craziest part is that the texture is tracked to the cameras motion which is what really confused me🤔. In camera? After effects? Is it possible to replicate cheaply? How the heck was this subtle stylish effect done?????
